<L>__{interior hitchcock house, bedroom night}
<A>__{hitch lies in bed, his thoughts racing as he waits for alma to come home. finally, the sound of the car comes up the driveway. he turns onto his side and pulls up the blankets, listening to the sound of the front door ... and alma's footsteps down the hall. she quietly slips into the bathroom and shuts the door before turning the light on. he watches her shadow through the strip of light at the bottom of door. when the bathroom light switches off again hitch hurriedly closes his eyes. alma emerges in her nightgown and stops at his bedside, peering down on him. she's not completely sure that he's actually awake, but she suspects.}
